(152, 6, 'Today it''s lucky to wear green.', 'วันนี้โชคดีที่ใส่สีเขียวครับ', 'Wan níi chôhk dii thîi sài sĭi khiăao khráp', 'day - this - luck - good - to - put on - colour - green - polite particle', 'The word ''thîi'' can have a variety of meanings including  ''at'', ''that'', ''which'' and ''for''. In Thailand each day of the week has a lucky and unlucky colour, a tradition based on Hindu mythology.', 'm6_18'),
